  "prompt": "Can I get infected with an STD from getting oral sex without protection?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to contract a sexually transmitted disease (STD) from receiving oral sex without protection. Certain STDs, such as herpes, gonorrhea, chlamydia, syphilis, and human papillomavirus (HPV), can be transmitted through oral sex. While the risk is generally lower compared to vaginal or anal sex, it is not zero. \n\nUsing protection, such as condoms or dental dams, can significantly reduce the risk of transmission. If you have concerns about STDs or potential exposure, it is a good idea to get tested and discuss your situation with a healthcare provider.",
